-- Argentina Authorizes $600 Million Increase in 2017 Bond Sale, Gazette Says
-- Bill Faries
-- 2010-06-18T11:26:12Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/argentina-authorizes-600-million-increase-in-2017-bond-sale-gazette-says.html

          
          
             Argentina’s Economy Ministry said it
is increasing the amount of 7 percent bonds due in 2017 that the
government can sell by $600 million.  
 The government announced the increase in a resolution
published in today’s official gazette.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
